Clone the main repository: git clone https://github.com/myproject.git
Checkout the r2.5.4 branch: git checkout r2.5.4
Create a new branch for the bugfix: git checkout -b r2.5.4.1-bugfix
Make changes to the code and commit them: git commit -am "Fix bug in r2.5.4"
Push the changes to the remote repository: git push origin r2.5.4.1-bugfix
Checkout the r2.5.5 branch: git checkout r2.5.5
Merge the bugfix branch into the r2.5.5 branch: git merge r2.5.4.1-bugfix
Push the changes to the remote repository: git push origin r2.5.5
Checkout the r3.0 branch: git checkout r3.0
Merge the bugfix branch into the r3.0 branch: git merge r2.5.4.1-bugfix
Push the changes to the remote repository: git push origin r3.0
